trans-unit.source: Wraps server controls that are not <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"></xref> controls so that they can appear and behave as true <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"></xref> controls at run time.
trans-unit.target: Bryter serverkontroller ikke <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"> </xref> kontrollerer slik at de kan vises og fungerer som true <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"> </xref> kontroller ved kjøretid.

trans-unit.source: The GenericWebPart control exists to provide a run-time wrapper for server controls that are not <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls, so that such controls can be used in Web Parts pages and applications.
trans-unit.target: Det finnes GenericWebPart-kontroll for å gi en kjøretid tekstbryting serverkontroller ikke er <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollerer, slik at slike kontroller kan brukes i webdeler sider og programmer.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: When developers add server controls--such as user controls, ASP.NET server controls, or existing custom controls--to a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> control, the GenericWebPart control automatically wraps the server controls at run time so they can exhibit the same functionality as true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls.
trans-unit.target: Når utviklere legger til serverkontroller--som brukerkontroller, ASP.NET serverkontroller eller eksisterende egendefinerte kontroller--til en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>kontroll, GenericWebPart kontrollen brytes automatisk av serverkontroller ved kjøretid slik at de kan ha samme funksjonalitet som true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>

trans-unit.source: The following table compares and contrasts GenericWebPart controls and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls.
trans-unit.target: Tabellen nedenfor sammenligner og står i kontrast GenericWebPart kontroller og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: |GenericWebPart control|<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control| |------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| |Exists to equip server controls that are not <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls with Web Parts functionality, so that any ASP.NET, custom, or user control can participate in Web Parts applications.|Exists to create custom ASP.NET controls that have native Web Parts functionality built in.
trans-unit.target: | GenericWebPart kontrollen | <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollen | |------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | Finnes for å utstyr serverkontroller ikke er <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Kontroller med webdeler funksjonalitet, så som alle ASP.NET, egendefinert eller kontroll kan delta i webdeler programmer. | Det finnes for å opprette egendefinerte ASP.NET-kontroller som har innebygd webdeler funksjonalitet som er bygd inn</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: This includes personalization, connections, import and export, and drag-and-drop capabilities.| |Is never declared in the markup of a page.
trans-unit.target: Dette omfatter personlige data, tilkoblinger, Importer og Eksporter og dra og slipp funksjoner. | | Er ikke deklarert i markup på en side.

trans-unit.source: It exists only to wrap server controls at run time, and to give the wrapped control (or child control) the full functionality of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.|Can be declared in the markup of a page at design time, like an ASP.NET server control, except that it is declared in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> zone.| |Includes and integrates its child control into the Web Parts personalization process so that it can act as a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Det finnes bare bryte serverkontroller ved kjøretid, og gi innpakket kontrollen (eller underordnet kontroll) all funksjonalitet i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>-kontroll. | Kan deklareres i markup på en side ved utformingen, som en ASP.NET-serverkontroll bortsett fra at det er deklarert i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>sone. | | Inkluderer og integrerer underordnede kontrollen i webdeler tilpassing behandle slik at den kan fungere som en true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: This occurs automatically, which makes it simple for developers to use server controls and user controls in Web Parts applications.|Is automatically included in the Web Parts personalization process.| |Can be accessed programmatically at run time (by using the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.GetGenericWebPart%2A> method and passing to it the child server control), like a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control or a standard ASP.NET control.|Can be accessed programmatically at run time, like a standard ASP.NET control.| Users benefit from the GenericWebPart control because it provides a consistent user experience.
trans-unit.target: Dette skjer automatisk, som gjør det enkelt for utviklere å bruke serverkontroller og brukerkontroller i webdeler programmer. | Automatisk er inkludert i webdeler tilpassing prosessen. | | Kan få tilgang til programmatisk på kjøretidspunktet (med metoden <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.GetGenericWebPart%2A>og sende til den underordnede serverkontroll) som en true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll eller en standard ASP.NET-kontroll. | Kan få tilgang til programmatisk ved kjøretid, som en standard ASP.NET-kontroll. | Brukere få glede av GenericWebPart kontrollen fordi den har en konsekvent brukeropplevelse.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.GetGenericWebPart%2A>

trans-unit.source: Any server control can be made to function like a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control, and will have the same consistent user interface (UI) elements such as verbs, icons, a title, and a header.
trans-unit.target: Serverkontroll kan gjøres skal fungere som en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>styre, og har samme konsekvent (UI) elementene i brukergrensesnittet som verb, ikonene, en tittel og et hode.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: Developers benefit from the GenericWebPart control because it enables them to reuse existing user controls and server controls within Web Parts applications.
trans-unit.target: Utviklere dra nytte av kontrollen GenericWebPart fordi det gjør det mulig for dem å bruke eksisterende brukerkontroller og serverkontroller i webdeler apper på nytt.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > When you create Web Parts pages, you do not have to do anything to enable an existing user control or custom control to be wrapped with the GenericWebPart control.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Når du oppretter webdeler sider, har du ikke gjøre noe for å aktivere en eksisterende brukerkontroll eller egendefinert kontroll for å være brutt med GenericWebPart kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: Simply add your server or user control to a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> zone, either programmatically or by declaring it in the page's markup, and the Web Parts control set automatically wraps your control with a GenericWebPart object at run time.
trans-unit.target: Ganske enkelt å legge til serveren eller bruker kontrollen til en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>sone programmatisk eller av deklarerer i sidens markup og webdeler kontrollen automatisk bryter kontrollen GenericWebPart objekter med på kjøretidspunktet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>

trans-unit.source: Because server controls that are placed in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> zones are wrapped with a GenericWebPart control at run time, developers can use ordinary server and user controls exactly as if they were <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls.
trans-unit.target: Fordi serveren styrer som er plassert i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>soner er står i en GenericWebPart-kontroll ved kjøretid, utviklere kan bruke vanlig server og brukerkontroller nøyaktig som om de var <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>

trans-unit.source: Note that, if you declare custom controls that inherit from the base <xref:System.Web.UI.Control> class within a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZone>, these controls cannot support the use of the intrinsic <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> properties.
trans-unit.target: Merk at hvis du angir egendefinerte kontroller som arver fra grunntallet <xref:System.Web.UI.Control>klasse i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZone>, disse kontrollene støtter ikke bruk av den innebygde <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Egenskaper.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZone> </xref:System.Web.UI.Control>

trans-unit.source: Thus, you cannot declare the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> properties on such controls, including properties such as the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Title%2A> property and the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Description%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: På denne måten du kan ikke deklarere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>Egenskaper på slike kontroller, inkludert egenskaper som den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Title%2A>egenskapen og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Description%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Description%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Title%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.source: In contrast, other types of server controls (such as <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls, user controls, and custom controls that inherit from <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl>) can declare these properties, because they support the use of expando properties.
trans-unit.target: I motsetning andre typer server kontrollerer (eksempel <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroller, brukerkontroller og egendefinerte kontroller som arver fra <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl>) kan deklarere disse egenskapene, fordi de støtter bruk av expando egenskaper.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: Expando properties are actually strings that can be added to a class dynamically as a property, by means of the <xref:System.Web.UI.IAttributeAccessor> interface.
trans-unit.target: Expando er faktisk strenger som kan legges til en klasse dynamisk som en egenskap ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Web.UI.IAttributeAccessor>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.IAttributeAccessor>

trans-unit.source: Controls that implement this interface, including the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl> class and its children, can use expando properties.
trans-unit.target: Kontroller som implementerer dette grensesnittet inkludert i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl>klassen og de underordnede objektene, kan bruke expando egenskaper.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl>

trans-unit.source: Because the base <xref:System.Web.UI.Control> class does not support expando properties, when a custom control that inherits from the <xref:System.Web.UI.Control> class is placed in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZone> and wrapped with a GenericWebPart control at run time, the Web Parts control set cannot dynamically add the intrinsic <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> properties to the custom control.
trans-unit.target: Fordi grunntallet <xref:System.Web.UI.Control>klassen støtter ikke expando egenskaper, når en egendefinert kontroll som arver fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.Control>klassen er plassert i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZone>og står i en GenericWebPart-kontroll ved kjøretid, webdeler kontrollen settet kan ikke dynamisk legge den innebygde <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>Egenskaper for egendefinert kontrollen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZone> </xref:System.Web.UI.Control> </xref:System.Web.UI.Control>

trans-unit.source: You have two choices in this case.
trans-unit.target: Har du to valg i dette tilfellet.

trans-unit.source: You can use the custom control without the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> properties, or you can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> interface in the custom control, enabling it to use the properties.
trans-unit.target: Du kan bruke den egendefinerte kontrollen uten den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>Egenskaper, eller du kan implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>for den egendefinerte kontrollen å aktivere den til å bruke egenskapene.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.source: As an example of how controls that inherit from <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl> can use the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> properties, if you declare an ASP.NET <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Calendar> control in the markup of a page (within a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> zone) at design time, even though this control does not inherit from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> class and does not natively contain <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> members, you can still treat it exactly like a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Som et eksempel på hvordan kontroller som arver fra <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl>kan bruke den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>Egenskaper, hvis du angir en ASP.NET <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Calendar>kontrollen i markup på en side (i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>sone) under utformingen, selv om kontrollen arver ikke fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>klasse og inneholder ikke opprinnelig <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>medlemmer, kan du fremdeles behandle den nøyaktig som en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Calendar> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebControl>

trans-unit.source: You can declare <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> properties on the calendar control, such as <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Title%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Description%2A>, and others.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Egenskaper i kalenderen kontrollere, for eksempel <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Title%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Description%2A>, og andre.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Description%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Title%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: At run time, you can use the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.GetGenericWebPart%2A> method, which returns the GenericWebPart control that is dynamically wrapping the calendar control, and work with it programmatically exactly as you would with a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control, with access to all the same properties, events, and methods.
trans-unit.target: Du kan bruke under kjøring av <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.GetGenericWebPart%2A>metode, som returnerer GenericWebPart kontrollen som er dynamisk wrapping Kalender-kontrollen, og arbeide med den programmatisk nøyaktig som med en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollere, med tilgang til de samme egenskapene, hendelser og metoder.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.GetGenericWebPart%2A>

trans-unit.source: The GenericWebPart control has a critical property that allows you to access its underlying server control: the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollen GenericWebPart har en kritisk-egenskap som gir deg tilgang til den underliggende serverkontrollen: den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A>

trans-unit.source: This property allows developers to programmatically access the server control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen gjør det mulig for utviklere å programmatisk tilgang til serverkontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A> property is also used by the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control to access personalization data from the child control, and to perform authorization, if the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> property is set.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A>egenskapen også brukes av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>kontrollerer tilgang til personlige data fra den underordnede kontrollen, og til å utføre godkjenning, hvis den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A>-egenskap er satt.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A>

trans-unit.source: The GenericWebPart control has several other properties, all of which override properties inherited from the base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> class.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollen GenericWebPart har flere andre egenskaper som overstyre arvet fra base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>klasse.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: As noted, you can use these properties with any child control, so that it can behave as a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Som er angitt, kan du bruke disse egenskapene med alle underordnede kontroller slik at den kan fungere som en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: One important property is the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.ExportMode%2A> property; it determines whether all the exportable properties, or only those marked as non-sensitive, can be exported.
trans-unit.target: Én viktig er den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.ExportMode%2A>egenskapen; fastsette om alle egenskapene som kan eksporteres, eller bare de merket som ikke sikkerhetsfølsom, kan eksporteres.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.ExportMode%2A>

trans-unit.source: The UI-oriented properties inherited from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> class, such as <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CatalogIconImageUrl%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Description%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Height%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.TitleUrl%2A>, and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Width%2A>, can be set in the declarative markup for any server control that is placed in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> zone.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapene UI-orientert arvet fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>class, for eksempel <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CatalogIconImageUrl%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Description%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Height%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.TitleUrl%2A>, og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Width%2A>, kan angis i den deklarerende markup for alle serverkontroll som er plassert i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase>sone.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Width%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.TitleUrl%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Height%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Description%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CatalogIconImageUrl%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: Important methods in the GenericWebPart class include the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CreateControlCollection%2A> method, which creates the collection of controls (including child controls) associated with a GenericWebPart control, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Render%2A> method, which delegates all rendering to the wrapped child controls.
trans-unit.target: Viktig metoder i klassen GenericWebPart inkluderer den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CreateControlCollection%2A>metode, som oppretter samlingen av kontroller (inkludert underordnede kontroller) tilordnet GenericWebPart kontroller, og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Render%2A>metode, som delegerer gjengivelse av alle til innpakket underordnede-kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Render%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CreateControlCollection%2A>

trans-unit.source: The constructors on the GenericWebPart class are protected and are intended either for internal use or for extensibility scenarios.
trans-unit.target: Konstruktører på klassen GenericWebPart er beskyttet, og er ment for internt bruk eller extensibility scenarioer.

trans-unit.source: There are some additional helpful insights for working with GenericWebPart controls.
trans-unit.target: Det er noen flere nyttige innsikt om arbeide med GenericWebPart kontroller.

trans-unit.source: If you want to set default values for the overridden properties in the GenericWebPart class, your user control or custom server control can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable> interfaces, and override their members.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi standardverdier for overstyrte egenskapene i klassen GenericWebPart, kontroll eller egendefinerte Serverkontroll kan implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable>grensesnitt, og overstyre medlemmene deres.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.source: At run time, the GenericWebPart control will get its values for the implemented properties from the child control that implements the interfaces.
trans-unit.target: Ved kjøretid får verdiene for egenskapene implementert fra den underordnede kontrollen som implementerer grensesnittene i GenericWebPart kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: If your control defines any of its properties as personalizable (by using the `Personalizable` metadata attribute), the GenericWebPart control automatically enables those properties for personalization at run time, just like the personalizable properties on a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Hvis kontrollen definerer en av egenskapene som bruke personlige data (ved hjelp av den `Personalizable` metadataattributt), GenericWebPart kontrollen aktiverer automatisk disse egenskapene for tilpassing ved kjøretid, akkurat som egenskapene bruke personlige data på en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: If you want to provide Web Parts editing features for your control, you can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable> interface.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi webdeler redigering funksjoner for kontrollen, kan du implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable>

trans-unit.source: At run time, when the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.CreateEditorParts%2A> method is called, the GenericWebPart control's code for the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.WebBrowsableObject%2A> property will call into the same property in the child control, and use the child control's implementation to create associated custom <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart> controls.
trans-unit.target: På kjøretid, når den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.CreateEditorParts%2A>-metoden, GenericWebPart kontrollens kode for den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.WebBrowsableObject%2A>egenskapen skal kall til den samme egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen, og bruke den underordnede kontrollen implementering til å opprette tilknyttede egendefinerte <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart>Kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.WebBrowsableObject%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.CreateEditorParts%2A>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control by passing in a reference to a control that becomes the child control.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontroll av sende i en referanse til en kontroll som blir den underordnede kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The GenericWebPart constructor is called by the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control in its <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.CreateWebPart%2A> method, to initialize an instance of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control by passing in a reference to a child server control.
trans-unit.target: Konstruktøren GenericWebPart kalles av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>kontrollerer i den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.CreateWebPart%2A>metode for å initialisere en forekomst av en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll av sende i en referanse til en underordnet serverkontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.CreateWebPart%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>

trans-unit.source: After the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> object is created, you can reference the child control using the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Etter den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>objekt er opprettet, kan du sjekke den underordnede styre ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>

trans-unit.source: A server control that becomes the child control of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control instance.
trans-unit.target: En serverkontroll som blir underordnede kontroll av den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontroll-forekomst.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the URL to an image that represents a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control in a catalog of controls.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir URL-adressen til et bilde som representerer en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen i en katalog for kontroller.

trans-unit.source: Web Parts applications often provide a catalog (or list) of controls that users can add to a page.
trans-unit.target: Deler webprogrammer inneholder ofte en katalog (eller liste) av kontroller som brukere kan legge til en side.

trans-unit.source: The CatalogIconImageUrl property on a control contains the URL to an image that represents the control when it appears in a catalog.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen CatalogIconImageUrl i en kontroll inneholder URL-adressen til et bilde som representerer kontrollen når det blir vist i en katalog.

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can access the property on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du har tilgang til egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: You can set values for the property on your control in the declarative markup of a Web page, as well as programmatically.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi verdier for egenskapen for kontrollen i deklarerende koden for en webside, samt som programmatisk.

trans-unit.source: To provide a default value for the property whenever the control is used, you can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> interface.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi en standardverdi for egenskapen når kontrollen er i bruk, kan du implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.source: A string that represents the URL to an image used to represent the control in a catalog.
trans-unit.target: En streng som representerer URL-adressen til et bilde som brukes til å representere kontrollen i en katalog.

trans-unit.source: The default value is an empty string ("").
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er en tom streng ("").

trans-unit.source: Gets a reference to the child control that is wrapped by a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control at run time.
trans-unit.target: Henter en referanse til den underordnede kontrollen brytes av en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontroll på kjøretidspunktet.

trans-unit.source: The ChildControl property provides the means to access the child control wrapped by a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen ChildControl gir mulighet til å få tilgang til den underordnede kontrollen står av en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control uses the ChildControl property to extract personalization data from the child control.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>kontrollen bruker egenskapen ChildControl til å trekke ut personlige data fra den underordnede kontrollen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.Control"></xref> that refers to the wrapped child control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.Control"> </xref> som refererer til den innpakket underordnede kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: Called by the ASP.NET page framework to notify server controls that use composition-based implementation to create any child controls they contain in preparation for posting back or rendering.
trans-unit.target: Kalles av ASP.NET siden framework skal varsles serverkontroller bruker sammensetningen implementeringen til å opprette alle underordnede kontroller de inneholder under forberedelsene for publisering tilbake eller gjengivelse.

trans-unit.source: Overrides the base method to create a read-only collection that consists of the child control wrapped by a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: Overstyrer metoden base for å opprette en skrivebeskyttet samling som består av den underordnede kontrollen står av en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The CreateControlCollection method creates a private, read-only collection that consists of a single control, which is the child control of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Metoden CreateControlCollection oppretter en privat, skrivebeskyttet samling som består av én kontroll, som den underordnede kontrollen for en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>

trans-unit.source: This collection is created so that developers cannot manually add other controls to a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne samlingen er opprettet, slik at utviklere ikke kan legge til andre kontroller til manuelt en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>

trans-unit.source: If you want to create a custom <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control without adding the child control to the private collection, you can derive from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> class, override the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.%23ctor%2A> constructor, and provide a different method for storing the child control referenced by the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil opprette en egendefinert <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll uten å legge til den underordnede kontrollen private-samlingen kan utledes fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>klasse, overstyre den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.%23ctor%2A>konstruktøren, og angi en annen metode for lagring av den underordnede kontrollen refererer til den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ChildControl%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.%23ctor%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.ControlCollection"></xref> that contains the child control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.ControlCollection"> </xref> som inneholder den underordnede kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: Returns a collection of custom <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart"></xref> controls that can be used to edit the child control of a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control when it is in edit mode.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en samling av egendefinerte <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart"> </xref> kontroller som kan brukes til å redigere underordnede kontroll av en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollerer når den er i redigeringsmodus.

trans-unit.source: The CreateEditorParts method is called when a control enters edit display mode.
trans-unit.target: Metoden CreateEditorParts kalles når en kontroll registrerer redigeringsmodus for visning.

trans-unit.source: This method overrides the base method inherited from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> class because, in the case of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control, it is the child control that is being edited, not the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control itself.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden overstyrer metoden base arvet fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>klasse fordi, med en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll, den er den underordnede kontrollen som er åpnet for ikke redigering, den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontrollerer seg selv.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: The CreateEditorParts method casts the child control to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable> interface, which enables the control to be edited.
trans-unit.target: Metoden CreateEditorParts kaster underordnede kontrollen i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable>grensesnittet som gjør det mulig for kontrollen som skal redigeres.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable>

trans-unit.source: This overridden method is what enables server controls that do not derive from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> class--including ASP.NET server controls, and custom server controls--to be edited as normal <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls.
trans-unit.target: Denne overstyrte metoden er hva aktiverer serverkontroller ikke avledet fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>klasse, inkludert ASP.NET serverkontroller og egendefinerte kontroller--som skal redigeres som normalt <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>Kontroller.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPartCollection"></xref> that contains custom <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart"></xref> controls associated with a server control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPartCollection"> </xref> som inneholder egendefinerte <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart"> </xref> Kontroller knyttet til en serverkontroll.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets a brief phrase that summarizes what a control does, for use in ToolTips and catalogs of server controls.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir et kort uttrykk som summerer hva en kontroll har, for bruk i verktøytips og kataloger av serverkontroller.

trans-unit.source: The Description property value is typically used as a descriptive string for a control in catalogs that provide lists of server controls, and as a ToolTip in a control's title bar.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapsverdien beskrivelse brukes vanligvis som en beskrivende streng for en kontroll i kataloger som gir lister over serverkontroller, og som et verktøytips i tittellinjen for en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: The content of the property appears in a ToolTip when a user positions the mouse pointer over the title text in a control's title bar.
trans-unit.target: Innholdet i egenskapen vises i et verktøytips når en bruker plasserer pekeren over tittelteksten i tittellinjen for en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can access the property on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du har tilgang til egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: You can set values for the property on your control in the declarative markup of a Web page, as well as programmatically.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi verdier for egenskapen for kontrollen i deklarerende koden for en webside, samt som programmatisk.

trans-unit.source: To provide a default value for the property whenever the control is used, you can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> interface.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi en standardverdi for egenskapen når kontrollen er i bruk, kan du implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.source: A string that briefly summarizes the control's functionality.
trans-unit.target: En streng som kort oppsummerer kontrollens funksjonalitet.

trans-unit.source: The default value is an empty string ("").
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er en tom streng ("").

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the height (in pixels) of a control.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir høyden på (i piksler) for en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can get or set the height on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du kan hente eller angi høyden på den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.Unit"></xref> that indicates the height of the control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.Unit"> </xref> som angir høyden på kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the ID of a control.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir IDen for en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: This value is not inheritable.
trans-unit.target: Denne verdien er ikke arvbare.

trans-unit.source: A string that contains the ID of the control.
trans-unit.target: En streng som inneholder IDen for kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: Delegates rendering the contents of the control to the child control.
trans-unit.target: Representanter gjengivelse av innholdet i kontrollen skal den underordnede kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlTextWriter"></xref> that represents the output stream to render HTML content on the client.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.HtmlTextWriter"> </xref> som representerer den utdata dataflyten som skal gjengi HTML-innhold på klienten.

trans-unit.source: Gets a string that is concatenated with the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title*> property value to form a complete title for a control.
trans-unit.target: Henter en streng som er slått sammen med den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title*>egenskapsverdien å lage en fullstendig tittel for en kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title*>

trans-unit.source: Use the Subtitle property optionally to return a standard subtitle string that will be appended to your custom <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control's title.
trans-unit.target: Bruke egenskapen undertittel eventuelt til å returnere en standard undertittel streng føyes til egendefinert <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontrollens tittel.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can access the property on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du har tilgang til egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: If you implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Subtitle%2A> property in a user control or custom control to provide a default value, the Web Parts control set automatically appends it to the value of the control's <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title%2A> property at run time to create a complete title.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du implementerer den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Subtitle%2A>egenskapen i en brukerkontroll eller en egendefinert kontroll for å angi en standardverdi webdeler kontrollen automatisk tilføyer dem til verdien for kontrollens <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title%2A>egenskapen på kjøretidspunktet vil opprette en fullstendig tittel.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Title%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart.Subtitle%2A>

trans-unit.source: A string that serves as a subtitle for the control.
trans-unit.target: En streng som fungerer som en Undertittel for kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The default value is an empty string ("").
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er en tom streng ("").

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the title of a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir tittelen på en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The visible title text in a part control's title bar is set by the Title property.
trans-unit.target: Synlig tittelteksten i delen kontrollens tittellinjen er angitt av egenskapen tittel.

trans-unit.source: If you do not supply a title for a control, the Web Parts control set automatically calculates a default string to use as a title.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du ikke angir en tittel for en kontroll, beregner webdeler kontrollen automatisk en standardstrengen som skal brukes som en tittel.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.DisplayTitle%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha mer informasjon, kan du se <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.DisplayTitle%2A>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.DisplayTitle%2A>

trans-unit.source: Also, it is possible to provide a default subtitle that is appended to the title string.
trans-unit.target: Det er også mulig å angi en standard undertittel som skal legges til en tittel-streng.

trans-unit.source: For details, see <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Subtitle%2A>.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon, kan du se <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Subtitle%2A>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.Subtitle%2A>

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can access the property on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du har tilgang til egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: You can set values for the property on your control in the declarative markup of a Web page, as well as programmatically.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi verdier for egenskapen for kontrollen i deklarerende koden for en webside, samt som programmatisk.

trans-unit.source: To provide a default value for the property whenever the control is used, you can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> interface.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi en standardverdi for egenskapen når kontrollen er i bruk, kan du implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er en tom streng ("").

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the URL to an image used to represent a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control in the control's own title bar.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir URL-adressen til et bilde som brukes til å representere en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen i tittellinjen kontrollens egen.

trans-unit.source: The TitleIconImageUrl property provides a way to associate an icon with a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen TitleIconImageUrl gjør det mulig å knytte et ikon med en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>

trans-unit.source: The icon appears in the control's own title bar.
trans-unit.target: Ikonet vises i tittellinjen kontrollens egen.

trans-unit.source: For thematic consistency, application developers often make this icon similar to the image that represents the control in a catalog of Web Parts controls (the image referenced in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CatalogIconImageUrl%2A> property).
trans-unit.target: For thematic konsekvens utviklere programmer ofte gjøre dette ikonet ligner på bildet som representerer kontrollen i en katalog med webdeler kontroller (bildet det refereres til i den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CatalogIconImageUrl%2A>egenskapen).</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.CatalogIconImageUrl%2A>

trans-unit.source: As it is implemented in the Web Parts control set, the TitleIconImageUrl property can be personalized by end users to change the image or icon that appears in a control's title bar.
trans-unit.target: Fordi den er implementert i kontrollen webdeler angitt TitleIconImageUrl egenskapen kan tilpasses etter sluttbrukerne mulighet til å endre bildet eller ikonet som vises i tittellinjen for en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can access the property on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du har tilgang til egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: You can set values for the property on your control in the declarative markup of a Web page, as well as programmatically.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi verdier for egenskapen for kontrollen i deklarerende koden for en webside, samt som programmatisk.

trans-unit.source: To provide a default value for the property whenever the control is used, you can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> interface.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi en standardverdi for egenskapen når kontrollen er i bruk, kan du implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.source: A string that represents the URL to an image.
trans-unit.target: En streng som representerer URL-adressen til et bilde.

trans-unit.source: The default value is an empty string ("").
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er en tom streng ("").

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets a URL to supplemental information about a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir en URL-adresse til tilleggsinformasjon en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: When you assign a URL to the TitleUrl property, the title of the control becomes a link.
trans-unit.target: Når du tilordner en URL-adresse til egenskapen TitleUrl, blir tittelen på kontrollen en kobling.

trans-unit.source: This property provides a convenient way for end users to access additional information about a control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen er det enkelt for sluttbrukerne mulighet til å få tilgang til mer informasjon om en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: The additional information could include copyright data, contact data, details about the creator of the control, or a summary of the purpose of a control.
trans-unit.target: Mer informasjon kan inkludere om dataene, kontakt data, detaljer om oppretteren av kontrollen eller et sammendrag av formålet med en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can access the property on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du har tilgang til egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: You can set values for the property on your control in the declarative markup of a Web page, as well as programmatically.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi verdier for egenskapen for kontrollen i deklarerende koden for en webside, samt som programmatisk.

trans-unit.source: To provide a default value for the property whenever the control is used, you can implement the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart> interface.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi en standardverdi for egenskapen når kontrollen er i bruk, kan du implementere den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebPart>

trans-unit.source: A string that represents a URL to more information about a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: En streng som representerer en URL-adresse til mer informasjon om en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The default value is an empty string ("").
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er en tom streng ("").

trans-unit.source: Gets a collection of custom verbs associated with a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: Henter en samling med egendefinerte verb som er knyttet til en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: Verbs derive from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerb> class, and provide user interface (UI) actions that users can perform on a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Verb som er avledet fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerb>klasse, og gi bruker brukergrensesnittet (UI) handlinger som brukere kan utføre på en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerb>

trans-unit.source: Usually, verbs are represented in the UI as buttons, links, or menu items.
trans-unit.target: Vanligvis vises verb som i Brukergrensesnittet som knapper, koblinger eller menyelementer.

trans-unit.source: There are standard verbs for opening, closing, editing, and minimizing a control, and other verbs for exporting a definition for the control or loading a Help file.
trans-unit.target: Det er standard verb for å åpne, lukker, redigere og minimere en kontroll og andre verb for eksport av en definisjon for kontrollen eller laste inn en hjelpefilen.

trans-unit.source: These verbs are not included in the Verbs collection, because the collection contains only custom verbs.
trans-unit.target: Disse verb inkluderes ikke i samlingen verb fordi samlingen inneholder bare egendefinerte verb.

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can access the property on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du har tilgang til egenskapen i den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: If you child control implements the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable> interface and thus overrides its <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable.Verbs%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control uses the child control's implementation when the Verbs property is invoked on the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du underordnede kontrollen implementerer den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable>grensesnittet og dermed overstyringer den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable.Verbs%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontrollen bruker den underordnede kontrollen implementering når egenskapen verb aktiveres på den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable.Verbs%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebActionable>

trans-unit.source: When you create custom verbs and add them to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.Verbs%2A> collection, you can then access the verbs programmatically from a Verbs control.
trans-unit.target: Når du oppretter egendefinerte verb og legge dem til i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.Verbs%2A>samling, kan du deretter åpne verbene programmatisk fra en verb-kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.Verbs%2A>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerbCollection"></xref> that contains custom <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerb"></xref> objects associated with a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerbCollection"> </xref> som inneholder egendefinerte <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerb"> </xref> objekter som er knyttet til en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The default value is <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerbCollection.Empty"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartVerbCollection.Empty"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Gets a reference to the child control, to enable the control to be edited by custom <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart"></xref> controls.
trans-unit.target: Henter en referanse til å aktivere kontrollen kan redigeres av egendefinerte kontrollen underordnede <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart"> </xref> kontroller.

trans-unit.source: If a child control implements the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable> interface, and overrides its <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.WebBrowsableObject%2A> property, when a user selects the control for editing, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control will call into the child control through the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.WebBrowsableObject%2A> property, and use the child control's implementation of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.CreateEditorParts%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Hvis en underordnet kontroll implementerer den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable>grensesnittet og overstyringer den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.WebBrowsableObject%2A>egenskapen, når en bruker velger kontroll for redigering av <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontrollen ringe til underordnede kontrollen via den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.WebBrowsableObject%2A>egenskapen og bruke den underordnede kontrollen implementering av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.CreateEditorParts%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.CreateEditorParts%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.WebBrowsableObject%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable.WebBrowsableObject%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IWebEditable>

trans-unit.source: This mechanism allows a server or user control that is not a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control to work with custom associated <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart> controls in a Web Parts application.
trans-unit.target: Denne mekanisme gjør det mulig for en server eller bruker kontroll som ikke er en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollen til å fungere med egendefinerte tilknyttede <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart>Kontroller i et webdeler-program.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Object> that consists of the child control of a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Object>som består av underordnede kontroll av en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart"> </xref> kontroll.</xref:System.Object>

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the width (in pixels) of the control.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir bredden på (i piksler) for kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: This property overrides the base property so that you can get or set the width on the child control as if it were a true <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen overstyrer egenskapen basistabellen slik at du kan hente eller angi bredden på den underordnede kontrollen som om det er sant <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.Unit"></xref> that indicates the width of the control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.Unit"> </xref> som angir bredden på kontrollen.
